It was here that members of the mock-Tudor Royal Selangor Club (1884), also designed by A. C. Norman, took time off from the affairs of the Empire to play cricket.
Among the many impressive skyscrapers, one of the most striking is the 35-story Dayabumi Complex (1970), southeast of Dataran Merdeka.
The square now hosts National Day state parades.
